offered another model.

354
00:25:28,826 --> 00:25:31,428
In his model, the Universe
expands.

355
00:25:31,495 --> 00:25:34,831
Expansion began at a point.

356
00:25:34,899 --> 00:25:37,668
All of of today's models allow
for an expanding Universe.

357
00:25:37,735 --> 00:25:41,238
Although I must add that not all
scientists are pleased with this.

358
00:25:41,305 --> 00:25:44,474
I am not sure I like it either.

359
00:25:44,541 --> 00:25:46,943
The idea of the Universe
appearing from nothing

360
00:25:47,011 --> 00:25:49,445
and perishing into collapse is
somewhat unnerving to me.

361
00:25:49,513 --> 00:25:50,981
How is it possible?

362
00:25:51,048 --> 00:25:53,350
Did the Universe begin at the
point?

363
00:25:53,417 --> 00:25:56,386
Did matter evolve from nothing?

364
00:25:56,453 --> 00:25:59,122
What was there before the
creation of the Universe?

365
00:25:59,190 --> 00:26:04,160
Do you know, young man, that
that particular question has
already been answered?

366
00:26:04,228 --> 00:26:07,597
Long before the birth of Albert
Einstein.

367
00:26:07,664 --> 00:26:10,600
No, I didn't. By whom?

368
00:26:10,667 --> 00:26:12,869
By St. Augustine.

369
00:26:12,937 --> 00:26:16,973
And what, in his opinion, was there
before the creation of the Universe?

370
00:26:17,041 --> 00:26:21,144
In his opinion, before the
creation of the Universe

371
00:26:21,212 --> 00:26:31,421
there was already a hell for
those asking such questions.

372
00:26:31,488 --> 00:26:33,990
But you are a world-renowned
physicist.

373
00:26:34,058 --> 00:26:39,996
